Verify Podman executor and support Podman over SSH

Fix the devcontainer Podman socket permissions so the non-root test user
can reach the rootful API service.

Fix re-entry so an existing pod uses its stored host before resolving
the current repo config, warn and ignore Podman runtime runArgs, and
clean up leftover Podman test containers after failed xtest cases.

Support Podman on SSH hosts.  Podman's own ssh:// transport needs
streamlocal forwarding (rejected by locked-down servers) and ignores
~/.ssh/config, so rumpelpod instead bridges a local proxy socket through
`ssh <host> podman system dial-stdio` and points the podman CLI at the
proxy.  The daemon keeps one proxy per SSH host; CLI-side interactive
exec starts an ephemeral one.  Covered by a new smoke test against a
locked-down sshd fixture serving a rootful Podman service.
